<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217219>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14 – 24. Myrmozercon michaeli Joharchi sp. nov., female. 14. Dorsal shield; 15. Dorsal seta enlarged (J 5) (not to scale); 16. Ventral idiosoma; 17. Tritosternum; 18. Hypostome; 19. Palp tarsal claw; 20. Epistome; 21. Chelicera; 22. femur II, dorsal aspect; 23. femur III, dorsal aspect; 24. femur IV, dorsal aspect." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/217219/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217217>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 7. Myrmozercon crinitus Joharchi sp. nov., female. 1. Dorsal shield; 2. Ventral idiosoma; 3. Hypostome; 4. Epistome; 5. Palp tarsal claw; 6. Tritosternum; 7. Chelicera." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/217217/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

